==English==

===Adjective===
'''short-lived'''

#A Not [[alive]] or [[existent]] for a long period of [[time]]
#:''"His joy was short-lived as he watched his fortunes change."''

====Pronunciations====

*[[IPA]]: /'short-ˈlaɪvd/ or /'short-'lĭvd/

:Linguists prefer /'short-'laɪvd/ as the [[term]] refers to a short [[life]] (a [[noun]]) rather than the [[past tense]] of [[live#Intransitive_verb|live]] (a [[verb]]).

